cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.DB

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper clearly involves the use of machine learning techniques to develop an early warning system for circulatory failure in the ICU.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper involves the application of computational techniques to analyze and predict patient data in the ICU.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques to develop an early warning system for circulatory failure in the ICU.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper discusses the limitations of human ability to process complex patient data in the ICU, and proposes an automatic system to assist clinicians in early detection of circulatory failure.
- cs.DB (Databases): The paper involves the use of a high-resolution ICU database with 240 patient years of data to develop and validate the early warning system.
